---
import ContentLayout from "../layouts/ContentLayout.astro";
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Totem â€” Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the Totem Chrome extension."
  ogUrl="https://usetotem.app/privacy"
  pageTitle="Privacy Policy"
  pageSubtitle="Last updated: February 23, 2026"
>
  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Overview</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Totem is a Chrome extension that replaces your new tab page with a calm reader for your X
        (formerly Twitter) bookmarks. Your privacy is fundamental to how Totem is built: all data
        stays on your device, and no information is sent to any external server operated by Totem.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Data collected</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Totem accesses the following data to function. All data is stored locally on your device
        using Chrome&apos;s built-in storage APIs and is never transmitted to any server controlled
        by Totem.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">X.com authentication tokens.</strong>{" "}
          When you browse x.com, Totem captures your authentication headers (OAuth bearer token,
          CSRF token, and session cookie) from requests to X&apos;s API. These tokens are stored
          locally and used exclusively to fetch your bookmarks from X&apos;s API on your behalf.
          They are never sent anywhere else.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">X.com user ID.</strong>{" "}
          Totem reads the{" "}
          <code class="rounded bg-x-card px-1 py-0.5 text-xs">twid</code>{" "}
          cookie from x.com to identify which account is logged in. This is stored locally to
          manage per-user bookmark data.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">Bookmark data.</strong>{" "}
          Your bookmarked posts are fetched from X&apos;s API and cached locally in your
          browser&apos;s IndexedDB storage for offline access and performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">Reading progress.</strong>{" "}
          Scroll positions and read states are saved locally so you can pick up where you left off.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">Preferences.</strong>{" "}
          Theme, layout, and display settings are stored in Chrome&apos;s local storage.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Permissions explained</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">cookies</strong> &mdash; Read the{" "}
          <code class="rounded bg-x-card px-1 py-0.5 text-xs">twid</code>{" "}
          cookie from x.com to detect which account is signed in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">storage</strong> &mdash; Save authentication tokens,
          preferences, and cached data locally.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">webRequest</strong> &mdash; Observe outgoing requests to
          X&apos;s GraphQL API to capture authentication headers and detect bookmark changes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">declarativeNetRequest</strong> &mdash; Set the correct
          Origin header on API requests made by the extension so X&apos;s servers accept them.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">tabs</strong> &mdash; Open a background tab to x.com when
          re-authentication is needed (e.g. after token expiry). The tab is closed automatically.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-x-text">host_permissions (x.com)</strong> &mdash; Required to read
          cookies, observe network requests, and make API calls to X.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Data sharing</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Totem does not transmit any data to servers owned or operated by Totem. The only network
        requests made are directly to X.com&apos;s API to fetch and manage your bookmarks, using
        your own authentication credentials. No analytics, telemetry, or tracking of any kind is
        included.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Data storage and security</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        All data is stored locally on your device using Chrome&apos;s extension storage APIs and
        IndexedDB. Authentication tokens are stored in{" "}
        <code class="rounded bg-x-card px-1 py-0.5 text-xs">chrome.storage.local</code>, which is
        sandboxed to the extension and inaccessible to websites or other extensions. Uninstalling
        the extension removes all stored data.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Third-party services</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Totem loads fonts from Google Fonts. No other third-party services are used. Wallpaper
        images are bundled with the extension and served locally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Changes to this policy</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        If this policy is updated, the changes will be posted on this page with a revised date.
        Continued use of the extension after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-x-text">Contact</h2>
    <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-pretty leading-relaxed text-x-text-secondary">
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, open an issue on the project&apos;s GitHub
        repository.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
